   <body>
      <p>After you have mapped at least one object, you can map fields between the corresponding mapped Dynamics 365 and Power objects.</p>
      <note type="note">
         <ul>
            <li>A maximum of 150 fields can be synced per object.</li>
            <li>You cannot use any of the following tasks to sync picklist fields between Dynamics 365 and Power. Refer to the topic <xref href="../mapping_picklist_field_va_143887218/143887218.xml"
                     format="dita">Mapping Picklist Field Values</xref> for complete steps.</li>
            <li>Before initiating an object sync, you must <xref href="../mapping_external_id_14388_143887216/143887216.xml"
                     format="dita">map an External Id field</xref> and <xref href="../mapping_modified_on_date__143887217/143887217.xml"
                     format="dita">map a ModifiedOn field</xref>.</li>
         </ul>
      </note>
